{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, efficiency issues arise when the group size becomes too large.",
    "Constructing more efficient ring signature schemes remains a challenge.",
    "In order to improve the lack of security in automatic payment systems, Chaum (1983) proposed a new cryptographic concept, blind signature, in 1982.",
    "Blind signature scheme consists of the interaction process between a user and a signer, that is, the user first performs a blind transformation to mask the original message, and then sends the transformed message to the signer to sign with the public key.",
    "In the end, the user performs a reverse transformation to obtain the signature corresponding to the original message."
  ]
}